 and from 1700 to the present day. The language's geographical variation both in the past and at the present time are fully documented and the sociolinguistic forces which lie behind linguistic innovation and its transmission provide a principal theme running through the book.WINNER of the Saltire society/National Library of Scotland Scottish Research Book of the Year Award  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aLanguage and culturezScotland. 0aScots languagexHistory. 4aLanguage & Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBaoill, Colm O, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeal, Joan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGregg, Robert J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJack, Ronald D. S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnston, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKniezsa, Veronika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacafee, C. I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeurman-Solin, Anneli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoessner, Lilo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMontgomery, Michael B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTulloch, Graham, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z97831107804750 cprintz978074860754940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978